            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "nvim uses the alternate screen, graphics are per screen. simply do a delete all placements (d=a/A) when exiting alternate screen. Use a for a suspend and A for an exit. This of course means for the case of suspend/resume all placements will need to be re-positioned on resume. \n\nAnd note that if you use image ids then deleting all placements of an image does not delete it form the terminal emulator, it just means that the image will be evicted on a priority basis in the future if the size of the image cache reaches its limit.",
