            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Maybe something like:\n\n`vim.ui.img.clear({ --[[ reserved, e.g. buf ]] })`\n\nI'm a bit worried about shared responsibility and edge cases like:\n\n```lua\nlocal id\nif false then id = 1 end\nvim.ui.img.del(id) -- deletes all images\n```\n\nThe bigger question is whether this API is even needed if we can iterate over all images anyway—then users can decide what to delete themselves. The only real issue is figuring out which images belong to a specific plugin.\n\nNamespacing is also great. `vim.ui.img.set({data_or_id}, {ns}, {opts})` feels right, but I'm not sure how deletion should work (`vim.ui.mg.clear({ns=?})`, `nvim_buf?_clear_namespace`, ...).\n\nSorry for the rookie opinion.\n\n---\nI also forgot to mention `vim.pack`. It has a similar API (`vim.pack.get/del`) and could serve as a useful reference.",
