            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> > especially if you wanted to distinguish neovim-created images versus other programs\n> \n> For the first pass, just a \"nuke it all\" functionality is good enough.\n\nI've got a potential PR for this ready, but before I push it for review did we want to discuss @drowning-cat thoughts more? Is the concern that if neovim crashed or something else happened that we'd not have the image ids to be able to clear them?\n\nIf so, @kovidgoyal mention of `a`/`A` to use on nvim exit would solve that unless it was such a hard crash that the autocmd didn't run. And I'd suspect at that point you would have bigger problems.\n\nThe PR I had added the `vim.ui.img.del(nil)` call to send `A` to delete all placements and images in terminal memory. Could gate that to just the exit autocmd instead.\n\nWhat are we solving for specifically with this one? Since I had the image ids, a user can't iterate through them to know what to clear. They'd have to keep track of the ids themselves.",
